# Frontend UI & design

When **designing or building** user-facing UI (new pages, layouts, dashboards, marketing surfaces, or any work where **visual/aesthetic choices** matter—not only logic):

1. **Read** the project skill (full instructions): `.cursor/skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md`
2. **Follow** that skill for typography, color, motion, layout, and avoiding generic “AI default” aesthetics.
3. **Scope**: This rule is tied to `**/*.vue` (Vue SFCs). If UI work lives in other files (e.g. `*.tsx`, `*.html`, global CSS), still **read the same skill** when the task is clearly UI/design-focused.

**Do not** treat backend-only changes as a trigger unless the user explicitly asks for UI.

### Reference

**Path (repo-relative):** `.cursor/skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md`